					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Laurie Hertzel</h4>
												<p>Laurie Hertzel spent 15 years as the books editor at the <em>Minneapolis Star Tribune</em> and now reviews books for the <em>Boston Globe</em>, the <em>Los Angeles Times</em> and—until a few days ago—the <em>Washington Post</em>. Her memoir, <em>News to Me: Adventures of an Accidental Journalist</em> (University of Minnesota Press, 2010) won a Minnesota Book Award. She is a past president of the National Book Critics Circle and has taught at the Loft Literary Center in Minneapolis and at Ohio State University. She is a Distinguished Professor of Practice in the low-residency MFA program in narrative nonfiction at the University of Georgia in Athens, Ga. Her second memoir, <em>Ghosts of Fourth Street</em>, will be published this spring by the University of Minnesota Press.</p>
